-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaking%20the%20spotlight%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Figuring%20out%20how%20much%20they'll%20need%20to%20pay%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-tips-overtime-trump-proposals-income-money-election-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaxes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20president%20and%20current%20GOP%20nominee%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20proposed%20a%20slew%20of%20changes%20to%20taxes%20and%20tariffs%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20are%20concerns%20his%20plan%20will%20have%20an%20uneven%20impact%20on%20Americans%20of%20different%20income%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fitep.org%2Fa-distributional-analysis-of-donald-trumps-tax-plan-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Institute%20on%20Taxation%20and%20Economic%20Policy%20%E2%80%94%20a%20left-leaning%20think%20tank%20%E2%80%94%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-cuban-trump-new-tax-cut-tariff-every-city-visit-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20and%20tariff%20proposals%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20spur%20an%20average%20tax%20cut%20of%20about%20%2436%2C300%20for%20the%20richest%201%25%20of%20Americans%2C%20or%20those%20with%20incomes%20of%20%24914%2C900%20and%20above.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20ITEP%20expects%20the%20next-richest%204%25%20to%20receive%20an%20average%20tax%20cut%20of%20about%20%247%2C200.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%2C%20the%20lowest-income%20quintile%20of%20Americans%20could%20see%20a%20tax%20increase%20of%20roughly%20%24800%20when%20factoring%20in%20how%20the%20tariffs%20would%20affect%20household%20costs%2C%20ITEP%20data%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FKwBns%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20tax%20changes%20by%20category%20of%20Trump's%20tax%20proposals%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22488%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20a%20dramatic%20shift%20of%20the%20burden%20from%20the%20top%20down%20to%20the%20middle%20and%20the%20bottom%2C%26quot%3B%20Ernie%20Tedeschi%2C%20the%20director%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20Yale%20Budget%20Lab%20and%20former%20chief%20economist%20at%20the%20White%20House%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisers%2C%20said%20of%20Trump's%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20looming%20expiration%20of%20former%20President%20Trump's%202017%20TCJA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tax-law-sinema-big-winner-bidens-social-spending-bill-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20sets%20up%20a%20big%20fight%20next%20year%20over%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20extend%20those%20tax%20cuts%20in%20part%20or%20in%20full.%20Trump's%20proposals%20include%20eliminating%20taxes%20on%20tips%20and%20overtime%2C%20extending%20the%202017%20tax%20cuts%20for%20individuals%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eimplementing%20higher%20tariffs%20on%20imported%20goods%2C%20and%20reducing%20the%20corporate%20tax%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20tariffs%20would%20likely%20hit%20households%20across%20the%20income%20spectrum%2C%20ITEP's%20analysis%20suggests%20that%20extending%20and%20even%20increasing%20the%202017%20tax%20cuts%20for%20the%20highest%20earners%20would%20more%20than%20offset%20those%20costs%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20net%20boon%20for%20the%20top%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Gardner%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20ITEP%2C%20explained%20how%20the%20think%20tank%20estimated%20the%20effects%20of%20tax%20and%20tariff%20changes%20on%20US%20taxpayers%20during%20a%20Monday%20call%20with%20reporters.%20Gardner%20said%20that%20the%20analysis%20used%20a%20computer%20model%20based%20on%20actual%20federal%20tax%20returns%20from%20the%20IRS%20to%20make%20estimates.%20Since%20some%20of%20Trump's%20proposals%2C%20like%20tariffs%2C%20have%20no%20direct%20connection%20to%20income%20tax%2C%20Gardner%20said%20ITEP's%20team%20worked%20extensively%20with%20data%20from%20other%20governmental%20sources%2C%20like%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%2C%20using%20similar%20techniques%20to%20other%20analyses%20of%20how%20tariffs%20affect%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20analysis%20assumes%20the%202017%20tax%20cuts%20will%20be%20extended%20%E2%80%94%20but%20Trump%20has%20previously%20claimed%20he%20would%20reverse%20the%20%2410%2C000%20cap%20on%20deducting%20state%20and%20local%20taxes%2C%20so%20ITEP's%20analysis%20included%20that%20reversal%20in%20their%20estimates%2C%20which%20further%20skews%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20tax%20proposals%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20income%20ladder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20studies%20have%20found%20similar%20potential%20impacts%20from%20the%20proposed%20tariffs%20on%20US%20families.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanprogressaction.org%2Farticle%2Ftrumps-tariff-would-cost-the-typical-american-household-roughly-1500-each-year%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%20found%20that%20Trump's%20proposals%20to%20impose%20tariffs%20across%20all%20imports%20could%20result%20in%20a%20%241%2C500%20tax%20increase%20for%20the%20typical%20American%20household%2C%20something%20that%20would%20disproportionately%20impact%20those%20with%20lower%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECasey%20B.%20Mulligan%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20economist%20for%20the%20White%20House%20Council%20of%20Economic%20Advisers%20under%20Trump%20and%20a%20current%20adviser%20at%20the%20right-leaning%20America%20First%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20estimated%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2F01%2F07%2Ftrump-economy-inflation-biden-campaign%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20proposal%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20additional%20percentage%20point%20in%20inflation.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxpolicycenter.org%2Ftaxvox%2Ftpc-trump-tariffs-would-raise-household-taxes-and-slow-imports%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETax%20Policy%20Center%20has%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20policies%20would%20bring%20down%20post-tax%20incomes%20by%20%241%2C800%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20still%20maintained%20that%20tariffs%20would%20not%20harm%20US%20consumers%20but%20rather%20raise%20prices%20for%20other%20countries.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Facyn%2Fstatus%2F1827139464906600538%3Fs%3D46%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20speech%20in%20August%20that%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20going%20to%20put%20tariffs%20on%20other%20countries%20coming%20into%20our%20country%2C%20and%20that%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20taxes%20to%20us.%20That%20is%20a%20tax%20on%20another%20country%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20Trump's%20other%20tax%20proposals%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-tips-overtime-trump-proposals-income-money-election-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeliminating%20taxes%20on%20tips%20and%20overtime%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20ITEP%20analysis%20found%20the%20proposal%20would%20help%20higher-income%20Americans%20over%20those%20who%20are%20lower-income%2C%20largely%20because%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20tipped%20workers%20don't%20make%20enough%20money%20to%20pay%20income%20tax%20and%20would%20not%20benefit%20from%20changes%20to%20the%20payment%20structure.%20Joe%20Hughes%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20on%20federal%20tax%20policy%20at%20ITEP%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20high-wage%20workers%20could%20take%20advantage%20of%20Trump's%20proposals%20to%20make%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E