22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20get%20a%20shot%20at%20a%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20those%20who've%20been%20working%20for%20a%20while%20%E2%80%94%20and%20those%20just%20starting%20out%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20unreasonable%20to%20wonder%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-managers-biased-against-gen-z-older-workers-survey-says-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eage%20bias%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20undercutting%20their%20career%20trajectory%20or%20prospects%2C%20labor-market%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20problem%20partly%20because%20the%20workforce%20in%20the%20US%20and%20many%20other%20developed%20countries%20is%20getting%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20estimated%20that%20about%20one%20in%20five%20people%2065%20and%20older%20in%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F12%2F14%2Folder-workers-are-growing-in-number-and-earning-higher-wages%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20working%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20was%20nearly%20double%20the%20portion%20of%20people%20that%20age%20who%20had%20a%20job%2035%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20people%20of%20various%20ages%20on%20the%20job%20together%20can%20be%20good%20for%20business.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Organization%20for%20Economic%20Cooperation%20and%20Development%20reported%20that%20promoting%20multigenerational%20workforces%20and%20giving%20older%20people%20more%20chances%20to%20work%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Fen%2Fpublications%2Fpromoting-an-age-inclusive-workforce_59752153-en.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20per%20capita%20gross%20domestic%20product%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%2019%25%20over%20the%20next%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%2287%25%20of%20occupational%20sectors%20have%20loosened%20their%20educational%20requirements%20on%20job%20postings%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20opening%20doors%20for%20people%20without%20a%20college%20degree.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6706ad583f2165d716df8f31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdvertisement%3Cp%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMarjorie%20Powell%2C%20chief%20HR%20officer%20and%20senior%20vice%20president%20at%20AARP%2C%20argued%20that%20people%20were%20working%20longer%20often%20out%20of%20necessity%2C%20to%20cover%20things%20like%20healthcare%20or%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20also%20continuing%20to%20work%20because%20they%20want%20to%20contribute%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerman's%20search%20for%20a%20new%20role%20in%20IT%20reflects%20a%20mix%20of%20necessity%20and%20desire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20three%20months%20after%20Berman%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20his%20wife%20also%20lost%20her%20job%20to%20corporate%20cutbacks.%20That%20left%20the%20couple%20with%20two%20mortgages%20and%20little%20income%20beyond%20their%20severance%20payments%20and%20unemployment%2C%20which%20ran%20out%20about%20six%20months%20ago%2C%20Berman%20said.%20Though%20they're%20renting%20out%20one%20of%20the%20homes%2C%20they're%20eating%20into%20their%20savings%20and%20investments%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerman%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20do%20some%20IT%20consulting%20work.%20To%20stand%20out%20from%20other%20job%20applicants%2C%20he%20has%20obtained%20certifications%20in%20artificial%20intelligence%20management%20and%20cybersecurity.%20Both%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20are%20considering%20pursuing%20an%20MBA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-wont-take-as-many-jobs-as-feared-altman-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erapid%20technological%20advances%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20exacerbate%20bias%20against%20older%20workers%20because%20being%20conversant%20in%20the%20latest%20thing%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20the%20preserve%20of%20the%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20think%20that%20the%20only%20people%20who%20are%20technology%20adapters%20are%20those%20that%20are%20in%20younger%20demographics%2C%20which%20is%20not%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20said%20other%20impediments%20to%20older%20workers%20could%20lurk%20in%20job%20descriptions%20with%20phrases%20like%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20native%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20energy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20often%20also%20ask%20job%20seekers%20when%20they%20were%20born%20and%20when%20they%20graduated%2C%20Powell%20said.%20She%20argued%20that%20with%20something%20like%20a%20degree%2C%20applicants%20should%20have%20to%20say%20only%20whether%20they%20completed%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Powell%20sees%20as%20pernicious%20language%20and%20requests%20for%20extraneous%20dates%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bred%20flags%20that%20there%20may%20be%20some%20age%20bias%20involved%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20older%20workers%20might%20be%20told%20they're%20overqualified.%20What%20employers%20might%20not%20understand%2C%20Powell%20said%2C%20is%20that%20those%20with%20loads%20of%20experience%20aren't%20always%20looking%20to%20keep%20climbing%20or%20nab%20ever%20higher%20pay.%20Instead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they%20may%20be%20drawn%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20work%20or%20the%20mission%20of%20an%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20either%20you%20have%20the%20qualifications%20to%20do%20the%20work%20or%20you%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20seen%20as%20overqualified%20is%20one%20of%20several%20concerns%20animating%20Don%20Trautman's%20job%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2067%2C%20he's%20old%20enough%20to%20retire%2C%20but%20he's%20been%20looking%20for%20part-time%20work%20on%20and%20off%20since%20April%20after%20taking%20a%20buyout%20from%20a%20longtime%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fdont75%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrautman%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20certified%20public%20accountant%20and%20holds%20an%20MBA.%20He%20spent%20the%20past%2018%20years%20managing%20buying%20and%20warehouse%20operations%2C%20though%20he'd%20like%20to%20return%20to%20the%20accounting%20work%20he%20did%20earlier%20in%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrautman%2C%20who%20lives%20with%20his%20wife%20outside%20Harrisburg%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20has%20removed%20most%20dates%20from%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20as%20some%20recruiters%20advise.%20Nevertheless%2C%20when%20he%20applies%20for%20jobs%2C%20he%20fills%20in%20the%20start%20and%20end%20dates%20for%20his%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20I%20start%20putting%20in%20that%20I%20started%20my%20last%20job%20in%20'99%20and%20I%20had%20multiple%20jobs%20before%20that%2C%20they're%20going%2C%20'Oh%2C%20wait%20a%20minute%2C'%26quot%3B%20Trautman%20told%20BI.%20It%20would%20be%20impossible%20not%20to%20deduce%20that%20he's%20an%20older%20worker%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20Trautman%20said%2C%20many%20employers%20advertise%20that%20they%20can%20offer%20room%20to%20advance%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20what%20he's%20seeking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20looking%20to%20become%20a%20CFO%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20Katerina%20Stroponiati%20founded%20Brilliant%20Minds%2C%20a%20venture-capital%20fund%20for%20founders%20over%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Stroponiati%20traveled%20to%20the%20US%20from%20her%20native%20Greece%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%20with%20dreams%20of%20starting%20a%20company%2C%20some%20of%20her%20family%20members%20asked%20whether%20she%20was%20too%20old%20to%20do%20something%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%2026%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStroponiati%2C%20who's%20now%2041%2C%20said%20she%20saw%20the%20stealthy%20reach%20of%20ageism%20at%20a%20prior%20venture%20fund%20she%20ran%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20few%20founders%20over%2050%20she%20encountered%20tended%20to%20intimate%20that%20they%20were%20out%20of%20place%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20always%20shy%2C%20and%20they%20were%20not%20as%20confident%20as%20those%20in%20their%2020s%2C%26quot%3B%20Stroponiati%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20she%20started%20her%20fund%20for%20older%20founders%20so%20that%20she%20could%20focus%20on%20an%20overlooked%20market%20and%20the%20ways%20people%20evolve%20throughout%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20headlines%20are%20around%20Gen%20Z%20trying%20to%20disrupt%20the%209-to-5%2C%26quot%3B%20Stroponiati%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20nobody%20talks%20about%20the%20other%20generations.%20Actually%2C%20boomers%20and%20Gen%20X%20are%20trying%20to%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20disrupting%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fund%20has%20received%20more%20than%20600%20applications.%20So%20far%2C%20she's%20invested%20in%20two%20startups.%20Both%20are%20run%20by%20women%20over%2055.%20One%20is%20focused%20on%20using%20a%20large%20language%20model%20in%20e-commerce%2C%20and%20the%20other%20involves%20AI%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStroponiati's%20goal%20is%20to%20invest%20in%2015%20companies%20by%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20offering%20an%20alternative%20to%20retirement%2C%20to%20the%20old%20model%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStroponiati%20argued%20that%20Greece%20didn't%20do%20enough%20to%20deal%20with%20an%20aging%20population%20and%20now%20faces%20economic%20and%20social%20consequences.%20The%20US%2C%20she%20said%2C%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20think%20what%20it%20means%20to%20have%20productive%20older%20citizens%2C%26quot%3B%20Stroponiati%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20North%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organizations%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20focuses%20on%20the%20challenges%20of%20having%20five%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20by%20some%20estimates%2C%20six%20%E2%80%94%20generations%20working%20side%20by%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20told%20BI%20that%20one%20difficulty%20for%20older%20workers%20is%20the%20long-held%20assumption%20in%20the%20US%20that%20people%20will%20retire%20around%20age%2065.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20safety%20nets%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20%26quot%3Bassume%20that%20you're%20not%20really%20supposed%20to%20be%20working%20after%20that%20certain%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20apart%20from%20recent%20deviations%20owing%20to%20factors%20like%20the%20pandemic%2C%20people%20in%20industrialized%20economies%20are%20generally%20living%20longer%20%E2%80%94%20and%20staying%20healthier%20as%20they%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20said%20many%20older%20workers%20are%20vibrant%2C%20skilled%2C%20and%20educated.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20discordance%20there%20between%20what%20our%20policies%20and%20expectations%20have%20in%20place%20versus%20what%20older%20adults%20objectively%20have%20to%20offer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20their%20part%2C%20North%20said%2C%20some%20younger%20workers%20and%20those%20hoping%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fentry-level-jobs-tech-roles-require-years-of-experience-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebreak%20into%20the%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20become%20frustrated%20that%20the%20oldest%20employees%20won't%20retire%20and%20create%20openings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20younger%20workers%20sometimes%20see%20older%20workers%20as%20%26quot%3Bblocking%20their%20own%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20that's%20fair%20or%20not%2C%20it's%20actually%20a%20pretty%20important%20debate%20to%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20North%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20frustration%20for%20many%20young%20people%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20challenges%20in%20paying%20for%20college%2C%20affording%20a%20home%2C%20and%20starting%20a%20family%20are%20tougher%20than%20they%20used%20to%20be.%20North%20added%20that%20resentments%20over%20those%20conditions%20could%20tee%20up%20%26quot%3Balarming%26quot%3B%20generational%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20a%20recipe%20for%20a%20society%20that%20is%20increasingly%20multigenerational%20to%20have%20these%20sorts%20of%20frictions%20and%20frustrations%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20age%20spectrum%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Trautman%2C%20who%20hopes%20to%20get%20back%20into%20accounting%2C%20returning%20to%20a%20fixed%20schedule%20on%20some%20days%20would%20be%20ideal.%20Now%20he%20completes%20his%20morning%20routine%20and%20sits%20down%20at%20his%20desk%2C%20but%20sometimes%20he%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20all%20honesty%2C%20retirement%20has%20been%20a%20struggle%2C%26quot%3B%20Trautman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20doesn't%20want%20to%20go%20work%20at%20Lowe's%20or%20Home%20Depot%2C%20as%20some%20friends%20have%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Bif%20it%20came%20down%20to%20it%2C%20I%20could%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Trautman%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20local%20grocery%20store%20is%20good%20about%20hiring%20people%20my%20age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbias-against-older-and-younger-workers-bad-for-business-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728489211000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6705a03b3f2165d716df6409%3Fformat%