3EInvestors%20use%20tax-loss%20harvesting%20to%20offset%20taxes%20on%20capital%20gains%20or%20income.%3Cp%3EDouglas%20Sacha%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20notes%20October%20as%20a%20key%20month%20for%20tax-loss%20harvesting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestors%20use%20tax-loss%20harvesting%20to%20offset%20taxes%20on%20capital%20gains.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETax-loss%20harvesting%20can%20also%20be%20used%20to%20offset%20income%20by%20up%20to%20%243%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20own%20any%20underperforming%20stocks%20or%20ETFs%20and%20want%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-season-strategies-how-to-use-stock-market-losses-advantage-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esave%20money%20on%20taxes%20next%20April%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20may%20be%20time%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20a%20popular%20strategy%20known%20as%20tax-loss%20harvesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20note%20Morgan%20Stanley%20published%20last%20week%2C%20October%20appears%20to%20be%20when%20investors%20most%20frequently%20employ%20the%20tax-savings%20method%20as%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20approaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20is%20fairly%20simple%3A%20if%20you%20own%20stocks%20that%20are%20down%20since%20you%20bought%20them%2C%20you%20can%20sell%20them%20and%20use%20that%20capital%20loss%20to%20offset%20your%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20ways%20to%20counter%20your%20tax%20bill%20through%20tax-loss%20harvesting.%20One%20way%20is%20by%20lowering%20your%20regular%20taxable%20income%20from%20things%20like%20salary%20or%20dividends.%20IRS%20rules%20allow%20you%20to%20reduce%20your%20taxable%20income%20by%20up%20to%20%243%2C000%20in%20a%20year%20from%20capital%20losses.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20realized%20%249%2C000%20in%20capital%20losses%20this%20year%2C%20you%20can%20spread%20that%20loss%20out%20over%20the%20next%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20larger%20potential%20benefit%2C%20according%20to%20Chris%20Chen%2C%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Insight%20Financial%20Strategists%2C%20comes%20through%20offsetting%20capital%20gains.%20The%20strategy%20could%20especially%20come%20in%20handy%20this%20year%2C%20with%20the%20stock%20market%20near%20all-time%20highs%20and%20several%20mega-cap%20firms%20seeing%20huge%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20offset%20capital%20gains%2C%20an%20investor%20would%20close%20out%20both%20a%20position%20that's%20down%20and%20a%20position%20that's%20up%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20cancel%20out%20taxes%20on%20the%20gain%20to%20the%20degree%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20loss.%20So%20a%20%242%2C000%20loss%20would%20cancel%20out%20a%20%242%2C000%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20IRS%20rule%2C%20one%20must%20then%20wait%2030%20days%20to%20reenter%20the%20position%20on%20the%20loss%2C%20while%20they%20can%20immediately%20buy%20back%20the%20position%20where%20they%20realized%20the%20gain.%20If%20the%20investor%20doesn't%20want%20to%20keep%20that%20cash%20on%20the%20sidelines%20during%20that%20month%2C%20however%2C%20they%20can%20move%20it%20into%20another%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Chen%20said%20that%20if%20an%20investor%20realizes%20a%20loss%20on%20Walmart%20but%20plans%20on%20buying%20back%20into%20the%20stock%20after%2030%20days%2C%20they%20might%20invest%20in%20shares%20of%20Target%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20as%20it%20offers%20exposure%20to%20a%20similar%20market%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c17eb9a9-b94d-411e-994c-ec543422354a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20use%20tax-loss%20harvesting%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Morgan%20Stanley%20note%2C%20stocks%20that%20are%20susceptible%20to%20downward%20price%20pressure%20due%20to%20tax-loss%20harvesting%20typically%20see%20the%20most%20downside%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStocks%20that%20analysts%20rate%20highly%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20therefore%20presumably%20widely%20held%20%E2%80%94%20and%20yet%20have%20fallen%20by%2010-25%25%20in%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%20the%20year%20typically%20underperform%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%201500%20and%20other%20similar%20stocks%20by%201-2%25%20in%20October%2C%20the%20note%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20timing%20is%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tax%20calendar%20is%20approaching%2C%20and%20investors%20want%20to%20lock%20in%20their%20losses%20to%20offset%20gains%20in%20case%20their%20losses%20shrink%20as%20the%20down%20positions%20start%20to%20recover%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20according%20to%20Chen%2C%20there%20is%20no%20right%20time%20to%20harvest%20a%20loss%2C%20and%20one%20should%20consider%20striking%20while%20the%20iron%20is%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20a%20strategy%20that%20should%20be%20used%20year-round%20depending%20on%20where%20the%20market%20is%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20happen%20to%20have%20a%20dip%20in%20the%20market%20in%2C%20say%2C%20March%2C%20that's%20a%20good%20time%20to%20do%20some%20tax%20harvesting%2C%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-savings-strategy-offset-gains-income-loss-harvesting-morgan-stanley-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728483140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df893090413ab8e1d79adf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-savings-strategy-offset-gains-income-loss-harvesting-morgan-stanley-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22October%20appears%20to%20be%20when%20investors%20most%20frequently%20employ%20the%20tax-savings%20method%20as%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20approaches.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-savings-strategy-offset-gains-income-loss-harvesting-morgan-stanley-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Less%20than%20half%20of%20Americans%20believe%20they're%20on%20track%20for%20retirement.%20Here's%20how%20to%20know%20and%20what%20to%20do%20if%20you're%20not.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20folder%20100%20dollar%20bill%20against%20a%20bright%20%20red%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a80acbaab37011780b81bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMost%20Americans%20are%20worried%20they%20will%20not%20achieve%20their%20retirement%20savings%20goals.%3Cp%3EDaryl%20Solomon%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20divide%20exists%20about%20reaching%20financial%20goals%20between%20confident%20and%20uncertain%20savers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInflation%20and%20market%20volatility%20are%20major%20obstacles%20to%20achieving%20retirement%20savings%20goals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStarting%20early%20and%20using%20tax-advantaged%20accounts%20can%20help%20meet%20retirement-savings%20targets.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20divide%20in%20America%20between%20the%20savers%20and%20investors%20who%20feel%20confident%20they're%20on%20track%20to%20achieve%20their%20financial%20goals%20and%20those%20who%20think%20they're%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20why%20there's%20so%20much%20media%20attention%20hovering%20around%20the%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20Rob%20Williams%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20for%20financial%20planning%20and%20wealth%20management%20at%20the%20Schwab%20Center%20for%20Financial%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20could%20be%20that%20as%20you%20get%20closer%20to%20retirement%2C%20reality%20and%20a%20feeling%20of%20running%20out%20of%20time%20start%20to%20sink%20in%3B%20a%20once%20optimistic%20outlook%20may%20get%20dampened.%20According%20to%20the%202024%20401(k)%20Participant%20Study%20by%20Charles%20Schwab%2C%20among%20boomer%20and%20Gen%20X%20respondents%2C%20only%2040%25%20felt%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bvery%20likely'%26quot%3B%20to%20achieve%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20goals.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20were%20more%20optimistic%2C%20at%2048%25%20and%2050%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERespondents%20cited%20inflation%20as%20the%20biggest%20obstacle%20to%20reaching%20retirement%20goals%2C%20followed%20by%20stock-market%20volatility%2C%20expenses%2C%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%20and%20child%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20creates%20a%20big%20question%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-much-do-i-need-to-retire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20do%20you%20need%20to%20save%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%20That%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20answer%20if%20the%20goal%20is%20a%20moving%20target.%20Retirement%20savers%20have%20to%20factor%20in%20a%20shifting%20inflation%20rate%20and%20planned%20and%20unplanned%20life%20events%2C%20including%20speculating%20on%20medical%20bills%20and%20even%20their%20life%20spans.%20It%20sounds%20like%20a%20daunting%20task%20laced%20with%20uncomfortable%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20around%20it%20is%20to%20take%20a%20quantified%20approach%2C%20which%20can%20be%20done%20by%20using%20the%20annual%20income%20multiplier%2C%20a%20scale%20that%20shows%20how%20much%20you%20should%20have%20saved%20for%20retirement%20based%20on%20your%20age.%20The%20Schwab%20Center%20for%20Financial%20Research%20assumes%20that%20following%20this%20scale%20would%20enable%20retirees%20to%20withdraw%2055%25%20to%2075%25%20of%20their%20income%20for%2030%20years%20after%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20table%20below%20demonstrates%20the%20amount%20required%20by%20each%20age.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you're%2035%20with%20an%20income%20of%20%24100%2C000%2C%20you%20should%20have%20between%20%24100%2C000%20to%20%24200%2C000%20set%20aside%20for%20retirement.%20Based%20on%20this%20scale%2C%20you%20can%20determine%20whether%20you%20have%20any%20catching%20up%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221412%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Table%20of%20annual%20income%20multiplier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67059c81a703186492806200%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22980%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECharles%20Schwab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20multiplier%20effect%20was%20tested%20using%20income%20ranges%20between%20%2450%2C000%20and%20%24300%2C000%2C%20beginning%20at%2025%2C%20it%20assumed%20that%20an%20investor's%20salary%20would%20rise%20annually%20based%20on%20a%202.28%25%20inflation%20rate%20until%2065.%20The%20saver%20must%20set%20aside%209%25%20to%2013%25%20of%20their%20income%20if%20they%20start%20on%20time.%20The%20investment%20strategy%20used%20for%20the%20study%20reflects%20a%20glide%20path%20portfolio%20that%20balances%20risk%20based%20on%20stocks%20and%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20the%20sooner%20you%20start%2C%20the%20easier%20it%20will%20be%20to%20meet%20the%20required%20amount%20for%20each%20age%20range.%20It%20follows%20the%20tried%20and%20true%20principle%2C%20which%20is%20that%20starting%20early%20allows%20a%20saver%20to%20leverage%20time%20in%20the%20market%2C%20even%20if%20the%20allocation%20is%20small.%20Over%20time%2C%20compound%20interest%20will%20balloon%20the%20principal%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20suggests%20really%20using%20up%20the%20tax-advantaged%20accounts%20with%20retirement%20savings%20vehicles%20such%20as%20401(k)s%20and%20making%20sure%20to%20max%20out%20the%20limit%20to%20get%20the%20employer%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20waited%20and%20you%20need%20to%20catch%20up%2C%20don't%20panic.%20Do%20what%20you%20can%20because%20every%20dollar%20you%20save%20and%20invest%20counts%2C%26quot%3B%20Williams%20said.%20Even%20if%20you%20haven't%20saved%20anything%20by%20the%20time%20you're%2050%2C%20you%20have%20at%20least%2015%20years%20to%20retire.%20This%20means%2C%20there's%20still%20time%20to%20ride%20out%20volatility%2C%20allowing%20you%20to%20add%20exposure%20to%20growth%20stocks%20that%20could%20help%20accelerate%20returns.%20Investors%20can%20also%20opt%20for%20target%20date%20funds%20that%20will%20slide%20toward%20less%20risk%20and%20more%20bonds%20as%20they%20get%20closer%20to%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you're%20over%2050%2C%20you%20have%20an%20added%20benefit%20called%20catch-up%20contributions.%20These%20allow%20you%20to%20allocate%20an%20additional%20%247%2C500%20to%20your%20401(k)s%20or%20403(b)%20and%20%243%2C500%20for%20a%20SIMPLE%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-formula-income-multiplier-best-ways-to-invest-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728483108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a80acbaab37011780b81bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-formula-income-multiplier-best-ways-to-invest-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Using%20an%20annual%20income%20multiplier%20is%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20determine%20if%20you%20are%20at%20the%20right%20amount%20for%20your%20age.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A66%2C%22canonica