20few%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20voters.%20Although%20Democrats%20are%20likely%20to%20win%20more%20votes%20overall%20(as%20they%20have%20in%20seven%20of%20the%20last%20eight%20presidential%20elections)%2C%20their%20ability%20to%20ensure%20higher%20voter%20turnout%20among%20their%20supporters%20in%20these%20swing%20states%20may%20well%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20the%20decisive%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EImpressions%20Over%20Issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20election%20campaign%20is%20being%20waged%20less%20on%20issues%20and%20more%20on%20impressions%20and%20attitudes.%20Trump%20is%20playing%20on%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20bureaucratic%20state%2C%20a%20scepticism%20of%20international%20entanglements%2C%20lower%20taxes%20for%20businesses%20and%20investors%2C%20curbs%20on%20immigration%2C%20and%20social%20conservatism%2C%20although%20he%20has%20attempted%20to%20dilute%20the%20latter%20to%20appeal%20more%20to%20moderate%20voters.%20Harris%20has%20positioned%20herself%20as%20appealing%20to%20youth%2C%20urban%20voters%2C%20ethnic%20minorities%2C%20responsible%20governance%2C%20and%20progressive%20social%20causes.%20Their%20competing%20worldviews%20reflect%20a%20rigid%20divide%20in%20American%20society%20across%20age%20and%20class%20lines%2C%20ethnic%20groups%2C%20and%20especially%20urban%20and%20rural%20constituencies%2C%20across%20which%20Republicans%20and%20Democrats%20have%20consolidated%20deeply%20entrenched%20if%20'big%20tent'%20coalitions.%20Suburban%20voters%2C%20white%20women%2C%20second-generation%20Hispanics%2C%20and%20union%20workers%20are%20among%20the%20constituencies%20in%20which%20Republicans%20and%20Democrats%20are%20still%20battling%20to%20sway%20opinion.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%202024%20US%20presidential%20election%20outcome%20will%20matter%20to%20India%2C%20although%20less%20directly%20perhaps%20than%20it%20will%20to%20some%20other%20countries%20and%20regions.%20For%20US%20adversaries%20(China%2C%20Russia%2C%20Iran%2C%20and%20North%20Korea)%20the%20election%20will%20determine%20negotiations%20over%20future%20relations.%20For%20US%20allies%20(NATO%20members%20in%20Europe%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20the%20Philippines%2C%20and%20Australia)%2C%20the%20election%20could%20signal%20changes%20to%20US%20force%20posture%2C%20assistance%2C%20and%20commitment.%20For%20those%20actively%20involved%20in%20current%20or%20prospective%20conflicts%20(Ukraine%2C%20Israel%2C%20Taiwan)%2C%20the%20outcome%20will%20determine%20the%20nature%20of%20US%20military%20aid.%20And%20for%20major%20trade%20partners%20(Mexico%2C%20ASEAN%2C%20the%20UK)%2C%20the%20election%20could%20have%20deep%20ramifications%20for%20their%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20Will%20Be%20Affected%2C%20But%20Not%20Directly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20less%20directly%20affected%20than%20many%20of%20these%20countries%2C%20not%20being%20an%20adversary%2C%20a%20treaty%20ally%2C%20or%20a%20country%20dependent%20on%20military%20or%20financial%20assistance%20from%20the%20United%20States.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20India%20is%20the%20United%20States'%20ninth-largest%20trade%20partner%20and%20enjoys%20about%20a%20%2430%20billion%20trade%20surplus%2C%20but%20its%20economy%20is%2C%20at%20present%2C%20less%20dependent%20on%20manufacturing%20exports%20than%20some%20other%20large%20emerging%20markets%2C%20such%20as%20Mexico%20or%20Vietnam.%20While%20the%20direct%20implications%20for%20India%20might%20be%20less%20than%20for%20others%2C%20the%202024%20US%20presidential%20election%20will%20undoubtedly%20have%20indirect%20effects%20on%20India.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnShould%20Trump%20be%20elected%2C%20India%20will%20have%20to%20confront%20some%20difficult%20negotiations%20over%20trade%20and%20immigration.%20Trump%20and%20his%20economic%20advisors%20have%20been%20clear%20that%20they%20will%20impose%20tariffs%20on%20countries%20they%20believe%20are%20engaging%20in%20unfair%20trade%20practices%2C%20especially%20China.%20But%20India%2C%20which%20enjoys%20a%20trade%20surplus%2C%20will%20also%20be%20subjected%20to%20some%2C%20resulting%20in%20retaliatory%20measures%20by%20New%20Delhi.%20Questions%20remain%20about%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20a%20second%20Trump%20administration%20can%20refashion%20trade%20policy%20without%20negative%20repercussions%20for%20the%20US%20economy%20-%20particularly%20for%20inflation.%20Moreover%2C%20Trump's%20advisors%20have%20pledged%20to%20stem%20immigration%2C%20especially%20by%20undocumented%20individuals%2C%20which%20may%20affect%20Indians%20too.%20Trump%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20impose%20restrictions%20on%20employment%20and%20student%20visas%20and%20cut%20funding%20for%20processing%2C%20contributing%20further%20to%20backlogs%20and%20delays.%20This%20will%20have%20implications%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20Indian%20businesses%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20Is%20Still%20The%20Big%20Question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20both%20Trump%20and%20Harris%2C%20whose%20views%20on%20foreign%20policy%20are%20still%20inchoate%20beyond%20a%20broad%20continuation%20of%20incumbent%20Joe%20Biden's%20approach%2C%20a%20primary%20determinant%20of%20their%20outlook%20will%20be%20their%20policy%20towards%20China.%20While%20Trump's%20national%20security%2C%20foreign%20policy%2C%20and%20trade%20advisors%20are%20overwhelmingly%20hawkish%20on%20China%20-%20suggesting%20a%20confrontational%20and%20competitive%20approach%20-%20some%20of%20his%20donors%20and%20financial%20associates%20have%20advocated%20for%20a%20more%20cooperative%20attitude%20and%20a%20cooling%20of%20US%20tensions%20with%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Harris%20has%20to%20contend%20both%20with%20hardening%20national%20security%20and%20trade%20impulses%2C%20as%20also%20with%20a%20progressive%20agenda%20among%20some%20Democrats%20that%20seeks%20to%20disassociate%20the%20United%20States%20from%20international%20competition%20and%20conflict.%20Progressives%20-%20as%20well%20as%20veterans%20of%20the%20Obama%20administration%20who%20hope%20to%20return%20to%20influence%20under%20Harris%20-%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20prioritise%20human%20rights%20over%20a%20balance%20of%20power%20in%20foreign%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Lot%20Would%20Depend%20On%20The%20Supporting%20Casts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20both%20Trump%20and%20Harris's%20approaches%20to%20China%20-%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20international%20affairs%20-%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20their%20selection%2C%20as%20President%2C%20of%20key%20advisors.%20The%20main%20Cabinet-level%20positions%20-%20U.S.%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20Defense%2C%20and%20Treasury%2C%20National%20Security%20Adviser%2C%20and%20U.S.%20Trade%20Representative%20-%20as%20well%20as%20second-%20and%20third-level%20political%20appointees%20will%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20set%20the%20tone%20for%20U.S.%20foreign%20policy%20for%20the%20next%20four%20years.%20Around%20Trump%2C%20figures%20such%20as%20Robert%20O'Brien%20and%20Robert%20Lighthizer%20are%20expected%20to%20play%20critical%20roles.%20The%20composition%20of%20a%20Harris%20foreign%20policy%20team%20is%20more%20uncertain%2C%20but%20it%20will%20likely%20be%20drawn%20from%20both%20Biden%20and%20Obama-era%20officials.%20Both%20Harris%20and%20Trump%20may%20also%20bring%20into%20their%20cabinets%20senior%20U.S.%20Senators%2C%20although%20that%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20margins%20in%20the%20Senate%20after%20this%20November's%20election.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnFor%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20developments%20of%20the%20next%20month%20-%20and%20the%20transition%20period%20between%20November's%20election%20and%20the%20next%20president's%20inauguration%20in%20January%20-%20will%20be%20observed%20carefully%2C%20in%20India%20and%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Dhruva%20Jaishankar%20is%20Executive%20Director%20of%20ORF%20America%20in%