ry%2Fwhy-a-meteorologist-was-reduced-to-tears-describing-hurricane-milton-13230750%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hurricane%20Milton%20reduced%20a%20US%20meteorologist%20with%2033%20years'%20experience%20reporting%20on%20hurricanes%20to%20tears%20live%20on%20air.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhy-a-meteorologist-was-reduced-to-tears-describing-hurricane-milton-13230750%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhy-a-meteorologist-was-reduced-to-tears-describing-hurricane-milton-13230750%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhy-a-meteorologist-was-reduced-to-tears-describing-hurricane-milton-13230750%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%2010%20Things%20That%20Cost%20Congress%20Haryana%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fjhaqo6c_haryana-congress_625x300_30_September_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20made%20history%20in%20Haryana%20by%20winning%20a%20record%20third%20term%2C%20defying%20all%20pollsters%2C%20and%20political%20pundits.%20Following%20a%20setback%20in%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20where%20the%20BJP%20lost%20five%20seats%20to%20Congress%2C%20the%20party%20went%20back%20to%20the%20drawing%20board%2C%20tightened%20its%20strategies%2C%20and%20quietly%20ran%20a%20campaign%20aimed%20at%20retaining%20the%20state%20and%20gaining%20pro-incumbency%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20held%20six%20months%20ago%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20leading%20in%2044%20assembly%20segments%2C%20while%20the%20Congress-Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20alliance%20was%20ahead%20in%2046%2C%20with%20respective%20vote%20shares%20of%2044%25%20and%2046%25.%20The%20trend%20of%20the%20BJP%20losing%20seats%20and%20vote%20share%20in%20state%20elections%20compared%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20gave%20Congress%20the%20confidence%20that%20it%20could%20win%20the%20state%2C%20leveraging%20support%20from%20wrestlers%2C%20farmers%2C%20and%20Agniveer%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20why%20exactly%20did%20Congress%20lose%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Overconfidence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20third%20state%20election%20after%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20where%20the%20Congress%2C%20projected%20as%20the%20favourite%2C%20suffered%20a%20shocking%20defeat.%20The%20party's%20defeat%20demonstrated%20that%20the%20BJP%20has%20the%20upper%20hand%20in%20direct%20one-on-one%20contests.%20Even%20with%20favourable%20conditions%2C%20victory%20cannot%20be%20declared%20until%20the%20last%20vote%20is%20counted.%20Many%20YouTube%20journalists%20predicting%20a%20Congress%20victory%20contributed%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20complacency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Factionalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntense%20factionalism%20plagued%20the%20party%2C%20with%20senior%20leaders%20Bhupinder%20Singh%20Hooda%2C%20Kumari%20Selja%2C%20and%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20at%20odds.%20The%20Hooda%20camp%20dominated%20ticket%20distribution%2C%20marginalising%20other%20factions.%20Selja%20abstained%20from%20campaigning%20for%20many%20days%2C%20prompting%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20to%20intervene%20at%20a%20rally%20to%20emphasise%20party%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Failure%20To%20Manage%20Rebels%20And%20Forge%20Alliances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20faced%2029%20rebels%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20which%20it%20failed%20to%20manage%20effectively.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20was%20in%20power%2C%20had%2019%20rebels.%20In%20Haryana%2C%20independents%20and%20smaller%20parties%20play%20a%20significant%20role%3B%20an%20analysis%20indicates%20that%2017%20of%20these%20rebels%20hurt%20the%20Congress's%20prospects.%20The%20AAP%2C%20which%20was%20an%20ally%20during%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20was%20not%20accommodated%20and%20claims%20it%20negatively%20impacted%20Congress%20in%20four%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Limited%20Benefits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202024%20general%20elections%2C%20Congress%20secured%2068%25%20of%20the%20Dalit%20and%2051%25%20of%20the%20OBC%20votes%2C%20leading%20to%20a%2014%25%20drop%20in%20BJP's%20vote%20share.%20In%20the%20state%20elections%2C%20Congress%20gained%20around%2011%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share%20largely%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20Jannayak%20Janta%20Party%20(JJP)%2C%20which%20was%20routed%20with%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20the%20vote%2C%20losing%2015%25%20compared%20to%202019.%20However%2C%20the%20JJP's%20vote%20share%20was%20concentrated%20in%20Hisar%20and%20Gurugram%2C%20limiting%20Congress's%20statewide%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20BJP%20increased%20its%20vote%20share%20from%2037%25%20to%2040%25.%20For%20the%20Congress%20to%20win%2C%20it%20needed%20to%20significantly%20dent%20the%20BJP's%20vote%20share%2C%20which%20it%20failed%20to%20do%20in%20the%20state%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Silent%20Non-Jat%20Consolidation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP's%20strategy%20of%20appointing%20Khattar%20and%20later%20Saini%20effectively%20engaged%20non-Jat%20voters.%20Brahmins%2C%20Baniyas%2C%20Khatris%2C%20OBCs%2C%20and%20certain%20SC%20groups%20believed%20they%20could%20only%20get%20a%20member%20from%20their%20community%20as%20Chief%20Minister%20through%20the%20BJP%2C%20not%20Congress.%20The%20dominance%20of%20the%20Hooda%20family%20may%20have%20contributed%20to%20a%20perception%20of%20Jat-centric%20politics%20within%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20influential%20community's%20discontent%20may%20have%20led%20some%20voters%2C%20unhappy%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20to%20refrain%20from%20switching%20to%20the%20Congress.%20The%20BJP%20successfully%20framed%20the%20contest%20as%20Jats%20versus%20non-Jats%2C%20reaping%20benefits%20in%20regions%20like%20Ahirwal%2C%20Braj%2C%20and%20the%20GT%20Road%20Belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Congress%20Couldn't%20Sweep%20Even%20the%20Jat%20Belt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2037%20seats%20where%20the%20Jat%20community%20comprises%20more%20than%2020%25%20of%20the%20electorate%2C%20located%20mainly%20in%20the%20Rohtak%20and%20Hisar%20divisions%2C%20there%20was%20a%20three-way%20split%20in%202019%20between%20Congress%20(14)%2C%20JJP%2FOthers%20(11)%2C%20and%20BJP%20(12).%20In%20this%20year's%20general%20elections%2C%20Congress%20benefited%20from%20the%20farmer%2Fwrestler%2Fyouth%20protests%2C%20establishing%20leads%20in%2027%20segments.%C2%A0Of%20the%2010%20seats%20the%20JJP%20lost%20in%202024%2C%20six%20went%20to%20Congress%20and%20four%20to%20BJP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20assembly%20polls%2C%20the%20honours%20were%20shared%20between%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP%20in%20this%20region%2C%20with%20independents%20and%20rebels%20from%20the%20Jat%20community%20impacting%20the%20Congress's%20tally%20in%20the%20region.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20BJP's%20Neutralisation%20Of%20Anti-Incumbency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP's%20losses%20in%20the%20general%20elections%20stemmed%20from%20discontent%20among%20certain%20voting%20segments%20regarding%20some%20policies.%20Instead%20of%20running%20a%20national%20campaign%2C%20the%20BJP%20fought%20a%20very%20localised%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20counter%20local%20anti-incumbency%2C%20the%20party%20replaced%20its%20chief%20and%2040%25%20of%20its%20MLAs.%20In%20contrast%2C%20Congress%20awarded%20tickets%20to%20all%20its%20incumbent%20MLAs%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20faced%20natural%20anti-incumbency%20due%20to%20perceived%20inaction%20in%20their%20constituencies.%20This%20strategy%20backfired%20for%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20RSS%20Support%20For%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20and%20BJP%2C%20which%20had%20previously%20been%20at%20odds%20during%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20reconciled%20their%20differences.%20In%20early%20September%2C%20the%20RSS%20launched%20a%20rural%20voter%20outreach%20programme%2C%20deploying%20at%20least%20150%20volunteers%20to%20each%20district.%20Between%20September%201%20and%209%2C%20the%20RSS%20conducted%20around%2090%20meetings%20in%20each%20Assembly%20constituency%20and%20nearly%20200%20meetings%20with%20party%20workers%20and%20rural%20voters%2C%20aiming%20to%20reinforce%20unity%20and%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Split%20Of%20The%20Dalit%20Vote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20captured%2068%25%20of%20Dalit%20votes%20in%20the%202024%20elections%20by%20warning%20that%20the%20BJP%20would%20change%20the%20constitution%20and%20end%20reservations%20if%20it%20gained%20power.%20This%20narrative%20was%20absent%20in%20the%20state%20polls.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20BJP%20won%20eight%20of%2017%20reserved%20constituencies%2C%20up%20from%20five%20in%202019%2C%20while%20Congress%20increased%20its%20tally%20to%20nine%20from%20seven.%20The%20JJP%2C%20which%20won%20four%20reserved%20seats%20in%202019%20and%20played%20a%20kingmaker%20role%2C%20ended%20with%20none%20this%20time.%20Congress%20and%20AAP%20had%20led%20in%2013%20of%20these%20seats%20during%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20four%20seats.%20Denying%20Kumari%20Selja%20a%20prominent%20position%20on%20Congress%20posters%20and%20in%20ticket%20distribution%20may%20have%20played%20a%20role%2C%20as%20the%20BJP%20framed%20this%20as%20an%20insult%20to%20Dalits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E10.%20Pro-Incumbency%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20no%20government%20can%20win%20a%20record%20third%20term%20without%20effectively%20working%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20positively%20impacting%20at%20least%20some%20segments%20of%20the%20population.%20The%20beneficiaries%20of%20various%20government%20schemes%20seemed%20to%20have%20backed%20the%20BJP%20due%20to%20the%20effective%20implementation%20of%20both%20central%20and%20state%20initiatives.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20people%20were%20pleased%20with%20the%20end%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ekharchi%20parchi%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20system%20in%20government%20recruitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20perfected%20the%20art%20of%20winning%20states%20where%20it%20has%20held%20power%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20through%20a%20combination%20of%20development%20work%2C%20strong%20organisation%2C%20and%20tactical%20manoeuvres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728466380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fjhaqo6c_haryana-congress_625x300_30_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2F10-things-that-cost-congress-haryana-6751195%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20the%20third%20state%20election%20after%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20where%20the%20Congress%2C%20projected%20as%20the%20favourite%2C%20suffered%20a%20shocking%20defeat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IRB%20Infrastructure%20to%20raise%20debt%20of%20up%20to%20%24200%20million%20via%20bond%20issue%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728466143000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farti